-- U.K. Braces for Further Flooding as Rainstorms Continue, PA Says
-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 2012-12-24T06:29:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/u-k-braces-for-further-flooding-as-rainstorms-continue-pa-says.html
U.K. weather forecasters predicted
further rainstorms and flooding, mainly in south and southwest
 England , as hundreds of homes and business were hit by floods,
the Press Association reported.  Heavy rain was reported in southwest England, falling on
already-sodden ground, and moving slowly northwards, the news
service said.  The Environment Agency maintained a severe flood alert for
the town of Helston, in Cornwall, where the River Coben burst
its banks and flooded hundreds of homes and businesses, the PA
said.  The EA has 145 flood warnings in place, mainly in central
England and the southwest.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  